# Cursor Rules for timeport-v4_payroll

## Code Style

- Use single quotes, avoid the use of double quotes and use consistent string literals to improve readability.
- Use TypeScript for all new files and components
- Follow React best practices and functional components with hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Prefer const assertions and type safety

## Project Structure

- Components should be placed in the `components/` directory
- Admin components go in `components/app/admin/`
- Member components go in `components/app/member/`
- Common components go in `components/common/`
- UI components go in `components/ui/`
- Use proper file naming with PascalCase for components

## Code Organization

- Keep components small and focused on single responsibility
- Use proper TypeScript interfaces and types
- Follow the existing schema structure in `schemas/`
- Use the existing utility functions in `lib/utils/`

## Next.js Specific

- Use App Router structure
- Place pages in appropriate route directories
- Use proper metadata and SEO practices
- Follow Next.js 13+ conventions

## Database and API

- Follow the existing schema patterns in `schemas/database/`
- Use proper error handling for API calls
- Implement proper loading states

## UI/UX Guidelines

- Maintain consistent design patterns
- Use the existing UI component library
- Ensure responsive design for mobile and desktop
- Follow accessibility best practices

## Code Quality

- Write clean, readable code
- Add proper comments for complex logic
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Follow the existing code patterns in the project
